    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a second referendum on using Alternative Vote (AV) for general elections",
        "additional_details": "The current system is not fair, and often means people end up voting tactically, rather than for their preferred candidate.\r\n\r\nUsing AV would mean if no candidate got 50% of the vote, the candidate with fewest votes is eliminated, and their votes allocated to the voters next preferred candidate. This process would then be repeated until a candidate had more than 50% of all votes.",
        "background": "Before the next General Election, the Government should hold a referendum on whether to change the voting system for general elections to Alternative Vote (AV).",
